column28: s5: Any  comment or feedback:

I like the idea of this game which shows what are all the possible consequenses of our actions during the outbreak of Corona virus and what it will lead to whether negativ or positiv results, and what we shall do!
I felt restricted and bound , the game should have more options.
Enjoyed the game a lot!
Lockdown measure indicates state incompetence dealing with crisis. South korea sets best example.
The photos were well chosen, the parameter was important to show even if the freedom was getting restricted the well being was improving

Maybe make the GUI a little better. Apart from that, not bad at all! Make the options a little different (meaning the same thing) but use different sentences to indicate them. Will make it more interesting

Maybe more could be done to make the game a better simulation of the real-life situation. The current version of the game operates on a binary "comply or resist" system which not only does not detail how the player resists these policies, but also assumes that the population as a whole acts in unison. Perhaps an element of randomness could be introduced, with a random portion of the population acting against the player's chosen option. In addition, the mode in which the player resists the government's policies could also be expanded upon, since resistance comes in various degrees (ignoring lockdown rules, not wearing masks, protests etc).
Funny game I did enjoy it
Very good
I did not understand what was the purpose of the game.

Sometimes the same governmental measures repeat even after declining them.
The word "surveillance " is better be more clarified. 
The measures looked random and independent of my previous choices.

The government was reacting to my decisions and I was reacting to its own which was confusing at times because I felt like we were moving in circles. The repetition in the government's reaction also threw me off because I didn't always know what to react to the same decisions. If there's a pretext or some sort of explanation perhaps contextualizing the game, such as giving more details on the political, social and economic situation of the country because I think decisions would differ greatly depending on the reality. Other than that, really good effort!
I would have liked if the game had more action like the game Plague Inc. It felt more like a questionnaire rather than a game.

The message of the game is quite clear, that is, a lot of countries are using the excuse of Covid-19 to restrict citizens from their daily lives. It had an interesting take on the subject. Their could be more variation in the game in terms of how the content of interface and text throughout the game, as it can be a bit repetitive. Also, it would be interesting to see more of a story line in the game. Nonetheless, the game has a powerful message, which can reach even those who did not suffer from strict restrictions during this pandemic. It's a game that makes you empathise with citizens suffering from unnecessary restrictions and helps you understand how this pandemic impacted countries differently.

Enjoyed the game! The pairing made it hard to differentiate between factors. For instance, "mass surveillance" is what I am very much against so once that was part of the two options paired all of my answers became "resist".

The idea in general is very nice in engagement of citizens with these kinds of issues, prompts though could be improved, also illustrations are repetitive which made me feel bored, dimensions of the images could be improved as well.

Alot of repetitive in government actions without explaining rationale behind it or simply add add actual numbers of infected people. I think adding more vivid scenarios would also make it bit more realistic and entertaining.
The game does get boring and does not impose challenge, the idea of intellectual's quotes though is a good educational tool I think.

I felt like the two options were showing the dichotomy of: this option or that option only (which is how the situation is presented). Yet there was no space for voicing out all the other complexities that has came up with the situation of Covid 19. That is, (me as a player) choosing to follow the government's measures or not.

If the intention of the music was to make the player stressed, the music was definitely chosen right. I felt trapped in a loop when the government decided to take the same measures the first couple of weeks. At some point I just decided to resist to see if something changes.

i noticed the quotes more that i noticed the pictures.
i also noticed the wording used in the sentences like surveillance
I am convinced that this crisis is being utilised to raise the level of citizens monitoring

The game is assigning an ulterior motive both to government action, and to my resistance (or not) to it. It's making the choice between "freedom" and "health" too much of an exclusive  compromise, whereas the presumed intention of governments is to maximize both for as many people as possible. Also, it makes it seem like government policy/action is a direct reaction to my personal choice to resist its measures, instead of guided by (hopefully) statistical analysis of the progression of the pandemic.
this was fun (and depressing)

Perhaps this is due to my interactions, however I though that I was doing something wrong since in consecutive weeks I was getting the same outcome, from the same input with no variation in the society status. I did followed the government indications, and in one moment  I though ok so.. is this endless maybe the aim of the game is to force me to make bad decisions... I was a little confuse. BTW, super important! the  music make the experience 300% more epic than what it would be without it, you fell under a lot of pressure which I found to be really immersive. Thank you for let me test it. Good Job!
I appreciated the quotes that appeared the most! Also, it would be easier to play if all of the images were the same size.
